\ab\af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f1\cf1\insrsid2700978\charrsid2700978 one monster, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\f1\cf1\insrsid2700978\charrsid2700978 Permanent: }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf1\insrsid2700978\charrsid2700978 This spell can
\par be cast on any monster, even if it is controlled or hired. It cannot be cast on a
\par character who has been transmorphized into a monster (he would be a
\par "character\'94 target, not a monster). This spell transmorphizes the spellcaster
\par into the monster he named as target. His items and horses are }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\f1\cf1\insrsid2700978\charrsid2700978 not
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf1\insrsid2700978\charrsid2700978 transmorphized.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf1\insrsid2700978 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf1\insrsid2700978\charrsid2700978 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f1\cf1\insrsid2700978\charrsid2700978 1. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf1\insrsid2700978\charrsid2700978 The spellcaster and monster become one entity, even when the spell is
\par inert. The spellcaster continues to be represented by his character counter,
\par but the absorbed monster simply ceases to exist - it is removed from play and
\par is put in the spell's spell box, where it remains until the spell ends. The
\par monster no longer functions as a monster: any denizens and Attention chits
\par assigned to it become unassigned, and it is released from any spells
\par bewitching it. It is not killed and cannot regenerate.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf1\insrsid2700978 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf1\insrsid2700978\charrsid2700978 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f1\cf1\insrsid2700978\charrsid2700978 1.1 }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf1\insrsid2700978\charrsid2700978 If the spellcaster is killed the monster is also killed. The killer gets the
\par spellcaster's points plus the monster's bounty points, without multiplication,
\par and both the spellcaster and the monster count as kills towards the killer's
\par daily total.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf1\insrsid2700978 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf1\insrsid2700978\charrsid2700978 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f1\cf1\insrsid2700978\charrsid2700978 1.2 }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf1\insrsid2700978\charrsid2700978 If the spell is broken without killing the spellcaster, the monster instantly
\par appears in the spellcaster's clearing.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf1\insrsid2700978 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf1\insrsid2700978\charrsid2700978 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f1\cf1\insrsid2700978\charrsid2700978 2. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf1\insrsid2700978\charrsid2700978 When the spell is energized, the spellcaster plays dummy chits and uses
\par the monster's combat values instead of his own. He must always use the
\par combat values that are on the face-up side of the monster's counter. If the
\par monster is Medium or Heavy, he can turn it either side up whenever he plays
\par a chit (it does not change tactics). If it is Tremendous, it turns red side up only
\par when it gets a hit; once it is red side up, he can turn it red side down
\par whenever he plays a chit. The counter automatically turns red side down
\par when he changes targets, or when his target is killed.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf1\insrsid2700978 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf1\insrsid2700978\charrsid2700978 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f1\cf1\insrsid2700978\charrsid2700978 2.1 }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf1\insrsid2700978\charrsid2700978 If the monster has a head or club, the spellcaster can play it during
\par combat as a second attack against his target. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf2\insrsid2700978\charrsid2700978 Heads and Clubs can be
\par played either side up, even when the body is red-side-up.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf2\insrsid2700978 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf2\insrsid2700978\charrsid2700978 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f1\cf1\insrsid2700978\charrsid2700978 2.2 }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf1\insrsid2700978\charrsid2700978 If the monster is a Demon or Imp with red side down, he casts its spell as
\par an attack (like a monster, not a character). He cannot change the spell it
\par casts. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\f1\cf1\insrsid2700978\charrsid2700978 Special: }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf1\insrsid2700978\charrsid2700978 When the spell is energized, the spellcaster can use the
\par monster's Magic type to record spells.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf1\insrsid2700978 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf1\insrsid2700978\charrsid2700978 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f1\cf1\insrsid2700978\charrsid2700978 3. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf1\insrsid2700978\charrsid2700978 If a spellcaster has duplicate Absorb Essence spells, he can absorb one
\par monster per spell. As each spell is energized, he transmorphizes into its
\par monster (so he will always be transmorphized into the monster that belongs
\par to the most recently energized spell). When the spells are energized
\par simultaneously, the spellcaster chooses which one transmorphizes him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f1\cf1\insrsid2700978\charrsid2700978 4. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf1\insrsid2700978\charrsid2700978 When Absorb Essence is cast by an Artifact or Spell Book, the item
\par transmorphizes when the spell becomes energized. The character holding
\par the item transmorphizes into the monster; if the item is not held by a
\par character, the item itself becomes the monster, and it functions like a normal
\par monster in all respects. When the monster is killed the spell is broken and the
\par item reappears.
